Sentencas: The present study deals with the citrate complexion synthesis of LAMOX-based Solid Oxide Fuel Cell (SOFC) electrolyte materials (La1.8Dy0.2Mo2-xWxO9 (x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.5, and 1), La1.8Dy0.2Mo2-xGaxO9 (x = 0.1 and 0.2), and La1.8Dy0.2Mo2-xVxO9 (x = 0.025, 0.05, 0.1, and 0.2)) and their characterization to understand the sintering behaviour and phase stability.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: From the dilatometer studies, the linear shrinkage and shrinkage rate of the LDMW (x = 0, and 0.1) showed better shrinkage than LM and LDM.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Gallium addition (LDMG) and Vanadium addition (LDMV) showed a negative impact on shrinkage behaviour.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the temperature range of 500-580 degrees C, the abrupt change in shrinkage rate showed the transition of phase from alpha to beta for the LM.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The modification of LM to LDM, LDMW, and LDMV suppressed the formation of the alpha phase.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: During thermal expansion behaviour study in the temperature range of 100-500 degrees C and 550-800 degrees C, the LM sintered pellet showed the coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) values of 13.3 x 10(-6)/degrees C and 21.6 x 10(-6)/degrees C respectively.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LDM and LDMW sintered pellets showed the CTE values in the range of 14-15 x 10-6/degrees C and 16-19 x 10-6/degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The relative density of the sintered pellets (1100 degrees C/5 h in air) (LM, LDM, LDMW, and LDMG (x = 0.1)) is found to be >90%.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It provides the suitability of these materials for further investigation as electrolytes of SOFCs/SOECs.
Titulo: Dilatometer studies on LAMOX based electrolyte materials for solid oxide fuel cells
